title: 820-3662 no chime
message:
If board doesn't boot at all, I doubt it will revive changing these chips.
Can you confirm USB activity for sure?
Use macOS installed on pendrive with Link LED; if flashes, is OK 100%.
Also do PRAM reset 2-3 times, if possible.

title: 820-3662 no chime

PLT_RESET_L comes up?
Pins 5 & 6 of U6100 go to 9V after 2-3s?
If yes, try known good BIOS.

title: 820-3662 no chime
message:
"PLT_RESET_L  1.3V "
Reset must be disabled, 3V is required there.
PCH doesn't finish power on sequence correctly.
Check PM_SYSRST_L, PM_PCH_PWROK and PM_PCH_SYS_PWROK.

title: 820-3662 no chime
message:
"PM_SYSRST_L  3.3v "
Then was a misstyping previous post?

Check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and their traces,
Clean J6199; or/and remove it if you don't use Medusa.
Try known good BIOS...
